## Impact & Legacy 🌟  
Hurston’s work reshaped Africana Studies, celebrating Black vernacular culture and challenging stereotypes, influencing writers like Toni Morrison and Alice Walker 🎭. Her focus on Black Southern life and folklore, preserved in the Smithsonian National Museum of African American History and Culture 🏛️, highlights cultural resilience ✊🏿. “Lion of Anacostia” detects bias in Hurston’s portrayals and critiques, ensuring accurate narratives for social justice—her legacy drives Python/AI analysis in modern Africana scholarship 📚.  

